{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011MHRfJX1oWjwe5B9LD1Bay","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The controller is v1.14.1. Let me check if `limit-reject-status` annotation is available in this version. I believe it was added in later versions.\n\nLet me also try just annotating with `limit-rps` to see if that works, and also try with `server-snippet` to see if that's disabled.\n\nActually, since configuration-snippet is disabled, let me think about another approach:\n\n1. Use the global ConfigMap to set `limit-req-status-code: \"429\"` - this would change the reject status for all rate-limited requests globally\n2. Use `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps` for the rate limit per Ingress\n\nThis seems like the right approach - set the global reject status code to 429 in the ConfigMap, and add the rate limit annotation to just the rate-api Ingress. The global setting would only affect rate-limited responses, so the health check would still return 200 since it's not being rate limited. Let me check what the exact ConfigMap option name is for setting the status code.\n\nI found it - `limit-req-status-code` in the ConfigMap defaults to 503, but I can change it to 429. So my plan is to patch the global ConfigMap with that setting and annotate the rate-api Ingress with the rate limit annotation.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":840,"cache_read_input_tokens":33506,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":840},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f833f063-feb7-4914-bc40-7ab86432fac9","uuid":"aed27978-cbd2-4dce-8d26-af714cd11940","request_id":"req_011CcL9rwKbuqyf4vKgo4TrA"}
