{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01M1CpGpvsQqiGvLhSpRJM65","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The annotation is there. Let me check the nginx controller logs to see why the rate limiting isn't working. There might be an error.\n\nActually, looking at the logs again, I saw this:\n```\nE0623 11:59:21.946329      11 main.go:96] \"invalid ingress configuration\" err=\"nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/configuration-snippet annotation cannot be used. Snippet directives are disabled by the Ingress administrator\" ingress=\"demo/rate-api\"\n```\n\nThis error was at 11:59:21. Then at 11:59:43, the ConfigMap was patched. At 11:59:47:\n```\nI0623 11:59:47.588362      11 main.go:107] \"successfully validated configuration, accepting\" ingress=\"demo/rate-api\"\n```\n\nSo the annotation was first applied without limit-rps, then somewhere the configuration-snippet was tried (maybe it was still in memory from the annotation command), then when the ConfigMap was patched, it revalidated without the snippet. Let me trace through the sequence again to understand what actually happened.\n\nThe first annotation command with both limit-rps and configuration-snippet failed due to the webhook error. Then I patched the ConfigMap to add the limit-req-status-code setting, and the second annotation with just limit-rps succeeded. The logs show an error about configuration-snippet at 11:59:21, which comes after all these steps, followed by the successful validation at 11:59:47. There might be some timing or caching issue at play here. The annotation is definitely present with limit-rps set to 1, so now I need to check if there's something wrong with how nginx is actually applying this configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":370,"cache_read_input_tokens":37710,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemera